   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>[Letter] 1824 Apr. 19, Washington [to] Mr. John Ross / Sam Houston</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>This document is a letter dated April 19, 1824 written by Sam Houston, future governor of Tennessee, to John Ross, future chief of the Cherokee Nation. Houston writes in response to some questions posed by Ross in regards to John Spears, an interpreter for the Cherokee who served as a delegate on behalf of the Arkansas tribe of the Cherokee. There is apparently a controversy involving Lewis Ross over whether or not Spears was entitled to receive a plot of land.</mods:abstract>
